149  /// \brief Calculate the "Indirect Address" for the given \p RegIndex and
150  /// \p Channel
151  ///
152  /// We model indirect addressing using a virtual address space that can be
153  /// accesed with loads and stores. The "Indirect Address" is the memory
154  /// address in this virtual address space that maps to the given \p RegIndex
155  /// and \p Channel.
156  virtual unsigned calculateIndirectAddress(unsigned RegIndex,
157  unsigned Channel) const = 0;
